      "solution": {
        "approach": "Design a command-based solution using 'free -h' which outputs human-readable memory statistics including total, used, free, shared, buff/cache, and available memory. This command is widely available on Linux systems and provides sufficient detail for stability assessment without requiring additional parsing logic. Ensure output is captured directly to stdout for immediate evaluation.",
        "algorithm": "Execute 'free -h' and capture its output stream",
        "complexity": "O(1)"
      },
